# Schedule Constraints

## Personal Work Schedule

- **Schedule:** [e.g., In-office Mon–Thu, 0700–1730]
- **Fitness Time:** [e.g., 3 hours/week of work-granted fitness time]
- **Preference:** [e.g., Early morning workouts on workdays]

---

## Caregiver / Childcare Constraints (if applicable)

If a household member's schedule blocks certain training days, configure a constraint calendar:

**Example situation:**
- Spouse/partner works [X]-hour shifts on rotating days
- Cannot train on those days due to childcare

**System integration:**
- Add a constraint calendar (ICS feed) to `config/calendar_sources.json`
- Set `"type": "constraint"` for the calendar entry
- Running workouts on constrained days are automatically rescheduled to another day in the same week

**Example config entry:**
```json
{
  "name": "Spouse Work Schedule",
  "url": "https://your-calendar-provider.com/calendars/your-ics-url",
  "enabled": true,
  "type": "constraint"
}
```

If no childcare constraint applies, leave the constraint calendar disabled or remove it.

---

## Workout Type Flexibility

**Inflexible (reschedule if blocked):**
- Running workouts — require dedicated time and specific conditions

**Flexible (can adapt around constraints):**
- Strength training — can be done in shorter blocks or at home
- Mobility work — can be done in small windows

---

## Inbox-Based Constraints

For one-off blocked days, drop a `.md` note in `vault/inbox/`:

```
# Blocked Days

No workout 2026-04-15 — family commitment
Rest day 2026-04-20 (travel)
```

See `vault/inbox/README.md` for supported keywords and date formats.

---

## Last Updated

- **Date:** YYYY-MM-DD
